{"id":8523,"date":"2017-11-28T15:15:19","date_gmt":"2017-11-28T23:15:19","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=8523"},"modified":"2017-11-28T15:15:19","modified_gmt":"2017-11-28T23:15:19","slug":"sitkum-lakes-mt-sitkum","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/11\/28\/sitkum-lakes-mt-sitkum\/","title":{"rendered":"SITKUM LAKES, MT SITKUM &#038; GOAT MOUNTAIN"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>A steep hike into an area of beautiful blue lakes and easy peaks. It is best done as an overnight trip.\u00a0<\/em><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Location:<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> C3\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation gain:<\/strong> 750m (2500&#8242;) to the lakes; 1200m (4000&#8242;) to the peak\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Key elevations:<\/strong> Summit Mt Sitkum 2420 (7950&#8242;)<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> 7-8kms to the lakes\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> June through October<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Access:<\/strong>\u00a0HC at end\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong> Season:<\/strong> late June through October<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82L\/8 Mt Fosthall\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive<\/strong>: Drive Hwy 6 to Frank&#8217;s Store, 50km east of Vernon.\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">0.0 Start north on Sugar Lake FSR.\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">16km Just before the dam, turn right on Kate Lake FSR<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">18.2km Stay right at fork. Keep left for next 6km.\u00a027.5km Road doubles back at creek and crosses it\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">28.1km Turn right on spur coming form behind.\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">37.1km Go left. Last few kms rough.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">42.1km End of road. Park for only 2-3 vehicles. Turning around difficult.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Trail:<\/strong> Walk up skid road and at 200m, cross creek (last water until lakes). Climb steeply for 45 minutes to a rough meadow with large boulders. Cross to an avalanche path with a sketchy trail up to another ridge. Traverse right and descend to the lakes. Mt Sitkum is about 3 hours return form the the lakes. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Or continue directly along the ridge to Mt Sitkum.\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Although this trip can be done as a day trip, it is best done as an overnight hike.\u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Climb Goat Mt, west of Mt Sitkum, up an obvious gully from the trail.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A steep hike into an area of beautiful blue lakes and easy peaks. It is best done as an overnight trip.\u00a0 Location: Difficulty: C3\u00a0 Elevation gain: 750m (2500&#8242;) to the lakes; 1200m (4000&#8242;) to the peak\u00a0 Key elevations: Summit Mt &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/11\/28\/sitkum-lakes-mt-sitkum\/